  "body": "Sometimes it work fine, but sometime i got the error. Code for tx signing:\r\n```\r\nconst trxOptions = {\r\n  to:    properties.getRaw('blockchain.target_address'),\r\n  value: web3.utils.toHex(web3.utils.toWei('0', 'ether')),\r\n  gas:   1509915,\r\n  data:  web3.utils.toHex(message)\r\n};\r\n\r\naccount.signTransaction(trxOptions)\r\n  .then(signedTx => {\r\n    console.log(signedTx.rawTransaction);\r\n    process.exit(0);\r\n  }).catch((ex) => {\r\n    console.error(ex);\r\n    process.exit(1);\r\n  });\r\n```\r\nCode refactoring below doesn't help:\r\n```\r\nweb3.eth.getGasPrice().then((gasPrice) => {\r\n  web3.eth.getBlock('latest').then((block) => {\r\n\r\n    const gasLimit = block.gasLimit;\r\n\r\n    const trxOptions = {\r\n      to:    properties.getRaw('blockchain.target_address'),\r\n      value: web3.utils.toHex(web3.utils.toWei('0', 'ether')),\r\n      gasPrice: gasPrice,\r\n      gas: gasLimit,\r\n      data:  web3.utils.toHex(message)\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    account.signTransaction(trxOptions)\r\n      .then(signedTx => {\r\n        console.log(signedTx.rawTransaction);\r\n        process.exit(0);\r\n      }).catch((ex) => {\r\n        console.error(ex);\r\n        process.exit(1);\r\n      });\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\nSo looks like utility methods (i mean `getGasPrice` and getting `gasLimit` from latest block) has no sense. How to sign tx in such way it will be accepted without the error?",
